g(x) = f(2x) - 3
Substituting f(x) = 2x + 1, we get: g(x) = [2(2x) + 1] - 3
Simplifying, we get: g(x) = 4x + 1 - 3
g(x) = 4x - 2
### Next: g(2)
Now, substitute x = 2 into g(x) = 4x - 2
g(2) = 4(2) - 2
g(2) = 8 - 2
g(2) = 6
### Next: g(g(2)) = g(6)
Substitute x = 6 into g(x) = 4x - 2
g(6) = 4(6) - 2
g(6) = 24 - 2
g(6) = 22
### Answer: g(g(2)) = 22
